# Where is ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable defined and how is it used during Raft log catch-up when a node tries to rejoin the cluster?

Here's the complete picture of `ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable` and its role in Raft log catch-up:

---

## Definition

`ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable` is defined in [`vendor/go.etcd.io/raft/v3/storage.go`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/r/github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/-/blob/vendor/go.etcd.io/raft/v3/storage.go?L36-38):

```go
// ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable is returned by the Storage interface when the required
// snapshot is temporarily unavailable.
var ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable = errors.New("snapshot is temporarily unavailable")
```

It's part of the `go.etcd.io/raft/v3` library (vendored in many repos including Kubernetes and Moby).

---

## Role in the `Storage` Interface

The [`Storage.Snapshot()`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/r/github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/-/blob/vendor/go.etcd.io/raft/v3/storage.go?L85-89) interface method is contractually expected to return this error when it needs more time to prepare a snapshot:

```go
// Snapshot returns the most recent snapshot.
// If snapshot is temporarily unavailable, it should return ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable,
// so raft state machine could know that Storage needs some time to prepare
// snapshot and call Snapshot later.
Snapshot() (pb.Snapshot, error)
```

The `MemoryStorage` implementation doesn't return this error (it always has a snapshot), but real on-disk storage backends (like etcd's `etcdserver`) do — typically while a snapshot is still being serialized or flushed to disk.

---

## The Catch-Up Flow

When a node rejoins the cluster after being down, the leader tries to replicate missing log entries via [`maybeSendAppend`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/r/github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/-/blob/vendor/go.etcd.io/raft/v3/raft.go?L616-660):

```go
func (r *raft) maybeSendAppend(to uint64, sendIfEmpty bool) bool {
    pr := r.trk.Progress[to]
    prevIndex := pr.Next - 1
    prevTerm, err := r.raftLog.term(prevIndex)
    if err != nil {
        // The log probably got truncated at >= pr.Next, so we can't catch up the
        // follower log anymore. Send a snapshot instead.
        return r.maybeSendSnapshot(to, pr)
    }
    // ...
    ents, err = r.raftLog.entries(pr.Next, r.maxMsgSize)
    if err != nil { // send a snapshot if we failed to get the entries
        return r.maybeSendSnapshot(to, pr)
    }
    // ... send MsgApp normally
}
```

If the required log entries have been **compacted away** (i.e., the follower is too far behind), both the `term()` and `entries()` calls fail, and execution falls through to [`maybeSendSnapshot`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/r/github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/-/blob/vendor/go.etcd.io/raft/v3/raft.go?L662-689):

```go
func (r *raft) maybeSendSnapshot(to uint64, pr *tracker.Progress) bool {
    if !pr.RecentActive {
        r.logger.Debugf("ignore sending snapshot to %x since it is not recently active", to)
        return false
    }

    snapshot, err := r.raftLog.snapshot()
    if err != nil {
        if err == ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable {
            r.logger.Debugf("%x failed to send snapshot to %x because snapshot is temporarily unavailable", r.id, to)
            return false   // ← gracefully back off, no panic
        }
        panic(err)         // ← all other errors are fatal
    }
    // ... send MsgSnap
    r.send(pb.Message{To: to, Type: pb.MsgSnap, Snapshot: &snapshot})
    return true
}
```

[`raftLog.snapshot()`](https://sourcegraph.sourcegraph.com/r/github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/-/blob/vendor/go.etcd.io/raft/v3/log.go?L291-296) first checks the in-memory unstable buffer, then delegates to the `Storage` backend:

```go
func (l *raftLog) snapshot() (pb.Snapshot, error) {
    if l.unstable.snapshot != nil {
        return *l.unstable.snapshot, nil
    }
    return l.storage.Snapshot()   // ← may return ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable
}
```

---

## Summary of the Catch-Up Sequence

| Step | What happens |
|------|-------------|
| 1 | Rejoining node's `pr.Next` is behind the leader's compacted log |
| 2 | `maybeSendAppend` fails to fetch entries/term → calls `maybeSendSnapshot` |
| 3 | Leader calls `raftLog.snapshot()` → `Storage.Snapshot()` |
| 4 | If storage isn't ready → `ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable` returned |
| 5 | `maybeSendSnapshot` logs a debug message and returns `false` (no panic, no send) |
| 6 | On the next heartbeat/bcastAppend tick, the leader retries |
| 7 | Once the snapshot is ready, `Storage.Snapshot()` succeeds → leader sends `MsgSnap` to the rejoining node |

The key design point: `ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable` is the **only non-fatal error** from `Storage.Snapshot()`. All other errors cause a panic. This gives storage backends a safe way to signal "not yet" without crashing the Raft state machine.

